states

private final java.util.Map<java.lang.Integer,CharacterState> states
The states that this character can have. For example, 0->"absent", 1->"present", 2->"one", or 3->"two". NOTE: it is legal to have non-contiguous integers in the keys - so, for example, you might have 0, 2, and 3.

protected Character resetPPodVersionInfo()
Description copied from class: PPodEntity
Mark this object's PPodVersionInfo for update to the next version number on save or update. This is done by setting it to null.

Implementors should also, if desired, call resetPPodVersionInfo() on any owning objects.
